title: Superior Sound of Elton John (1970-75) [FLAC]
description:
From the liner notes:

"In an effort to keep up with the new technology in recorded sound, [Original Porducer] Gus Dudgeon has recently spent five weeks in D.J.M. Recording Studios remixng a large portion of Elton John's back catalogue from the original multi-tracks into the new Digital Stereo format.

He has tried to keep the mixes identical to the originals but, with the benefit of all the latest advanced technological equipment, the quality of the sound has moved this timeless music into a new dimension of listening enjoyment."

This 1983 out-of-print album is presented in lossless FLAC format with Replay Gain, EAC log and Dynamic Range analysis.
